BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:24172329c69511474d319073978cf4548f0d816b@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T033558Z
DTSTART:20260625T123000Z
DTEND:20260625T130000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, May 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\n\nExplainer:\n• 
 What it is: Core PCE Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices paid 
 by consumers for goods and services\, excluding food and energy.\n\n• 
 Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish f
 or USD and bearish for bonds\, because it can increase expectations of t
 ighter Federal Reserve policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Core PCE is one 
 of the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measures\, so it can strong
 ly influence interest-rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly\, usu
 ally released about four weeks after the month ends.\n\n• Notes: Core 
 PCE differs from Core CPI because it uses a different basket and weighti
 ng method. CPI often gets more immediate market attention\, but Core PCE
  is very important for Fed policy.\n\n• Acronyms: PCE = Personal Consu
 mption Expenditures\; CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: ht
 tps://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ics
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, May 2026
END:VALARM
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:30 minutes: 🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, May 20
 26
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:159349de5e3db2ee93d7591f08e3467dfd554916@macro-calendar.local
DTSTAMP:20260603T033558Z
DTSTART:20260625T123000Z
DTEND:20260625T130000Z
SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: GDP (Third Estimate)\, Industries\, Corporate Profit
 s\, State GDP\, and State Personal Income\, 1st Quarter 2026
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\n\nExplainer:\n• 
 What it is: Gross Domestic Product\n\n• Measures: Broad change in the 
 value of goods and services produced by the economy.\n\n• Usual market
  effect: Stronger-than-forecast GDP can be bullish for the local currenc
 y and equities\, although the reaction depends on inflation and rate exp
 ectations.\n\n• Why traders care: GDP is the broadest measure of econo
 mic growth and helps traders judge whether the economy is accelerating o
 r slowing.\n\n• Frequency: Quarterly\, with revisions.\n\n• Notes: G
 DP can be backward-looking\, so markets often react more strongly when t
 he result changes the outlook for central-bank policy or recession risk.
 \n\n• Acronyms: GDP = Gross Domestic Product.\n\nOfficial source: http
 s://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.ics
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT24H
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Tomorrow: 🔥 US BEA: GDP (Third Estimate)\, Industries\, Co
 rporate Profits\, State GDP\, and State Personal Income\, 1st Quarter 20
 26
END:VALARM
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT30M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:30 minutes: 🔥 US BEA: GDP (Third Estimate)\, Industries\, 
 Corporate Profits\, State GDP\, and State Personal Income\, 1st Quarter 
 2026
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
